.SH NAME
anvil-watch-bonds \- Tools to monitor the state of bonded network interfaces
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anvil-watch-bonds 
\fI\,<command>
.SH DESCRIPTION
This tool provides a concise way to monitor the state of bonded network interfaces. 
.IP
.SH OPTIONS
\-?, \-h, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this man page.
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-secure\fR
When logging, record sensitive data, like passwords.
.TP
\-v, \-vv, \-vvv
Set the log level to 1, 2 or 3 respectively. Be aware that level 3 generates a significant amount of log data.
.IP
.SH "Commands:"
\fB\-\-run\-once\fR
Normally, this program stays active, updating every two seconds. If this switch is used, it shows the status once and exits.
.IP
